These guys are great and such fantastic service!  First off, I am picky with my sandwiches, I know this.  I ordered a Gargantuan with lettuce, cheese, meat, and cilantro only.  I asked for please no sauces of any kind.  My order was delivered with mayonnaise.  I called in, informed that there was "sauce" on it, and please send another with no "sauce."  Another sandwich was delivered with mayonnaise.  I called back and asked for a refund.  They obliged.  A few minutes, the manager called, apologized about the two mix up's, and explained that "sauce" meant "oil and vinegar" to their staff.  I understand the confusion, and he acknowledged that I made it clear only lettuce, cheese, meat, and cilantro was ordered.  They refunded me as planned, and Sent me a Third sandwich with my specifications. I am so very impressed at the customer service at this location and just had to let everyone know that this was the only (of many sandwiches ordered) one that deviated from my order, and Jimmy John's went to great lengths to remedy it.  Thank you all!  Very content customer here.  :D

The sandwiches are decent but their ability to follow basic instructions is far below average. I order online fairly often and each time I check the box requesting mustard packets, and each time they let me down. Upon ordering today I noticed that the box for condiments was missing, so I added a delivery note requesting some mustard (which was spelled out on the middle of the receipt I received). Upon receiving my sandwich today I saw the my receipt which asked for mustard and I asked the delivery gal if there was mustard in the bag. Her response was "there should be" and then she was out the door in less than 2 seconds.  As a sandwich company like JJ's, I'd imagine bringing condiments wouldn't be such a complicated task but apparently this is a consistent problem with them.

Italian Night Club is easily the best fast food deli sandwich out there.  The bread is a little crisp on the outside, and all soft and chewy on the inside.  Tons of meat and cheese.  I had to get use to eating these though.  Something about how they put the mayo on makes all the meat and cheese want to slide out one side after each bite.  You have to pinch one end for every bite to stop the sliding.  And be careful, at least for me these are only a once a week or so treat.  The sodium level in those preserved meats makes my heart start thumping in my chest.  Just checked: 2334mg, 34 mg over your entire daily recommended value. Also, those freaky fast commercials are not joking.  The last sandwich I ordered got here in a little over 7 minutes.  I have been in drive through lines longer than that.  Crazy.
